        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 3:22PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Groveton, or 20 miles southwest of Apple Springs, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Apple Springs, Trinity, Groveton, Kennard, Sebastopol, Pennington,
and Centralia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
